Manila Water  Co., the utility
serving half of the Philippine capital, said it signed a $100-million loan with the International Finance Corp.  The 18-year loan will fund the construction of water and
sewerage treatment plants, Manila Water said in a disclosure to
the stock exchange. It is the companyâ€™s fourth loan from
International Finance since 2003 and is the longest the World
Bank unit has provided to the Philippine water sector, Manila
